Israel has a unit responsible for monitoring and alerting people of incoming projectiles called the homefront command.
Each time any projectile enters Israeli airspace, whether it be a drone or a missile, people projected to be in the area where it’s projected to fall recieve notifications via several channels I.e mobiles, tvs, radio etc.
This happens within sufficient time to ensure civilians can find the best shelter they can given the individual circumstances. 
Those who are traveling on the road or are not close to a physical shelter are instructed to hunker down until a notification is received saying the threat has passed, just like this girl is doing.
